<section id="origins">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>The Origins of Tea</h2>
      <p>Tea (<span class="chinese-char">茶</span>, chá) is China's gift to the world. The tea plant (<em>Camellia sinensis</em>) originated in the mountainous region of southwest China &mdash; present-day Yunnan, Sichuan, and Guizhou &mdash; where wild tea trees thousands of years old still stand today. Legend credits the mythical emperor <strong>Shennong</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">神農</span>) with discovering tea around 2737 BCE when leaves from a wild tree blew into his pot of boiling water.</p>
      <p>While the Shennong legend is apocryphal, reliable historical evidence of tea consumption dates to the <strong>Han Dynasty</strong> (206 BCE &ndash; 220 CE). Initially valued as a medicinal brew, tea gradually evolved into a daily beverage and, by the Tang Dynasty, into a cultural institution of the highest order.</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>茶的起源</h2>
      <p>茶（<span class="chinese-char">茶</span>，chá）是中國贈予世界的瑰寶。茶樹（<em>Camellia sinensis</em>）原產於中國西南部的山區 &mdash; 即今日的雲南、四川與貴州一帶 &mdash; 至今仍有樹齡數千年的野生古茶樹屹立其間。傳說中，神話時代的帝王<strong>神農</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">神農</span>）約於公元前2737年偶然發現了茶：野茶樹的葉片恰好飄落入他正在煮沸的水中。</p>
      <p>神農嘗茶之說雖屬傳說，但可靠的茶飲歷史文獻記載可追溯至<strong>漢代</strong>（公元前206年 &ndash; 公元220年）。茶最初作為藥飲受到重視，其後逐漸演變為日常飲品，至唐代更發展為登峰造極的文化制度。</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>茶的起源</h2>
      <p>茶（<span class="chinese-char">茶</span>，chá）是中国赠予世界的瑰宝。茶树（<em>Camellia sinensis</em>）原产于中国西南部的山区 &mdash; 即今日的云南、四川与贵州一带 &mdash; 至今仍有树龄数千年的野生古茶树屹立其间。传说中，神话时代的帝王<strong>神农</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">神農</span>）约于公元前2737年偶然发现了茶：野茶树的叶片恰好飘落入他正在煮沸的水中。</p>
      <p>神农尝茶之说虽属传说，但可靠的茶饮历史文献记载可追溯至<strong>汉代</strong>（公元前206年 &ndash; 公元220年）。茶最初作为药饮受到重视，其后逐渐演变为日常饮品，至唐代更发展为登峰造极的文化制度。</p>
</div>
    </section>

    <section id="cha-jing">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>Lu Yu and the Cha Jing</h2>
      <p>The transformation of tea from a simple drink into a refined cultural practice owes everything to <strong>Lu Yu</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">陸羽</span>, 733-804 CE). His <em>Cha Jing</em> (<span class="chinese-char">茶經</span>, Classic of Tea), written during the Tang Dynasty around 760 CE, is the world's first comprehensive treatise on tea.</p>
      <p>Across ten chapters, Lu Yu codified every aspect of tea culture:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The botanical nature and ideal growing conditions of the tea plant</li>
        <li>Tools for harvesting and processing tea leaves</li>
        <li>The proper methods of manufacture (Tang Dynasty tea was compressed into cakes, ground to powder, and whisked)</li>
        <li>The ideal water sources, ranked by quality (mountain spring water first, river water second, well water last)</li>
        <li>Detailed brewing procedures with precise equipment specifications</li>
        <li>The philosophical dimension of tea drinking as a practice of simplicity and mindfulness</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Lu Yu elevated tea to the level of the arts. After his work, tea drinking was no longer mere refreshment &mdash; it was <strong>cha dao</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">茶道</span>), the Way of Tea.</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>陸羽與《茶經》</h2>
      <p>茶從一種簡單的飲品蛻變為精緻的文化實踐，當歸功於<strong>陸羽</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">陸羽</span>，733-804年）。他的《<em>茶經</em>》（<span class="chinese-char">茶經</span>，Classic of Tea），撰成於唐代約760年，是世界上第一部系統論述茶的專著。</p>
      <p>全書十章，陸羽將茶文化的方方面面一一規範：</p>
      <ul>
        <li>茶樹的植物特性與理想的種植環境</li>
        <li>採摘與加工茶葉的器具</li>
        <li>正確的製茶方法（唐代之茶壓製成餅，碾磨成末，擊拂而飲）</li>
        <li>理想水源的品第排列（山泉水為上，江河水次之，井水為下）</li>
        <li>精確的煮茶程序與器具規格</li>
        <li>飲茶作為簡樸與正念修行的哲學維度</li>
      </ul>
      <p>陸羽將茶提升至藝術的境界。自其著作問世後，飲茶不再僅是解渴之事 &mdash; 而是<strong>茶道</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">茶道</span>），即茶之大道。</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>陆羽与《茶经》</h2>
      <p>茶从一种简单的饮品蜕变为精致的文化实践，当归功于<strong>陆羽</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">陸羽</span>，733-804年）。他的《<em>茶经</em>》（<span class="chinese-char">茶經</span>，Classic of Tea），撰成于唐代约760年，是世界上第一部系统论述茶的专著。</p>
      <p>全书十章，陆羽将茶文化的方方面面一一规范：</p>
      <ul>
        <li>茶树的植物特性与理想的种植环境</li>
        <li>采摘与加工茶叶的器具</li>
        <li>正确的制茶方法（唐代之茶压制成饼，碾磨成末，击拂而饮）</li>
        <li>理想水源的品第排列（山泉水为上，江河水次之，井水为下）</li>
        <li>精确的煮茶程序与器具规格</li>
        <li>饮茶作为简朴与正念修行的哲学维度</li>
      </ul>
      <p>陆羽将茶提升至艺术的境界。自其著作问世后，饮茶不再仅是解渴之事 &mdash; 而是<strong>茶道</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">茶道</span>），即茶之大道。</p>
</div>
    </section>

    <section id="dynasties">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>Tea Through the Dynasties</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tang Dynasty (618-907)</strong> &mdash; Tea becomes a national beverage. Compressed tea cakes are ground and boiled with salt. Tea tax is instituted. Tea spreads to Japan via Buddhist monks.</li>
        <li><strong>Song Dynasty (960-1279)</strong> &mdash; The golden age of tea aesthetics. Powdered tea is whisked in bowls (the ancestor of Japanese matcha). Tea competitions (<span class="chinese-char">鬥茶</span>, dòuchá) judge colour, aroma, and froth. Emperor Huizong writes a treatise on tea.</li>
        <li><strong>Ming Dynasty (1368-1644)</strong> &mdash; Emperor Hongwu abolishes compressed tea cakes in favour of loose-leaf tea. This revolution introduces <strong>steeping</strong> as the primary brewing method. The Yixing teapot (<span class="chinese-char">宜興壺</span>) emerges as the ideal vessel. Tea gardens of Fujian, Zhejiang, and Anhui become legendary.</li>
        <li><strong>Qing Dynasty (1644-1912)</strong> &mdash; Gongfu tea ceremony formalises in Fujian and Guangdong. Oolong and pu-erh tea production flourishes. The global tea trade expands via European colonial powers, profoundly shaping world history.</li>
      </ul>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>歷代茶事</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>唐代（618-907年）</strong> &mdash; 茶成為舉國之飲。團餅茶經碾碎後加鹽煎煮。朝廷始徵茶稅。茶經佛教僧侶東傳日本。</li>
        <li><strong>宋代（960-1279年）</strong> &mdash; 茶藝美學的黃金時代。末茶以茶筅擊拂於盞中（即日本抹茶之濫觴）。鬥茶之風盛行（<span class="chinese-char">鬥茶</span>，dòuchá），以茶色、茶香與湯花高下定勝負。宋徽宗親撰茶論。</li>
        <li><strong>明代（1368-1644年）</strong> &mdash; 明太祖朱元璋廢團茶而改散茶。此一變革確立了<strong>沖泡</strong>為主要的製飲方式。宜興紫砂壺（<span class="chinese-char">宜興壺</span>）應運而生，成為品茗至器。福建、浙江、安徽諸省茶園名聞天下。</li>
        <li><strong>清代（1644-1912年）</strong> &mdash; 工夫茶藝在福建和廣東定型。烏龍茶與普洱茶的生產蓬勃發展。茶葉經歐洲殖民列強之手行銷全球，深刻影響了世界歷史的走向。</li>
      </ul>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>历代茶事</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>唐代（618-907年）</strong> &mdash; 茶成为举国之饮。团饼茶经碾碎后加盐煎煮。朝廷始征茶税。茶经佛教僧侣东传日本。</li>
        <li><strong>宋代（960-1279年）</strong> &mdash; 茶艺美学的黄金时代。末茶以茶筅击拂于盏中（即日本抹茶之滥觞）。斗茶之风盛行（<span class="chinese-char">鬥茶</span>，dòuchá），以茶色、茶香与汤花高下定胜负。宋徽宗亲撰茶论。</li>
        <li><strong>明代（1368-1644年）</strong> &mdash; 明太祖朱元璋废团茶而改散茶。此一变革确立了<strong>冲泡</strong>为主要的制饮方式。宜兴紫砂壶（<span class="chinese-char">宜興壺</span>）应运而生，成为品茗至器。福建、浙江、安徽诸省茶园名闻天下。</li>
        <li><strong>清代（1644-1912年）</strong> &mdash; 工夫茶艺在福建和广东定型。乌龙茶与普洱茶的生产蓬勃发展。茶叶经欧洲殖民列强之手行销全球，深刻影响了世界历史的走向。</li>
      </ul>
</div>
    </section>

    <section id="six-types">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>The Six Categories of Chinese Tea</h2>
      <p>Chinese tea is classified into six categories based on the degree and type of processing, particularly <strong>oxidation</strong>:</p>
      <table class="elements-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Category</th><th>Chinese</th><th>Oxidation</th><th>Famous Examples</th><th>Character</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Green</td><td>綠茶 Lǜchá</td><td>None</td><td>Longjing, Biluochun, Huangshan Maofeng</td><td>Fresh, vegetal, sweet</td></tr>
          <tr><td>White</td><td>白茶 Báichá</td><td>Minimal</td><td>Silver Needle, White Peony</td><td>Delicate, subtle, honeyed</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Yellow</td><td>黃茶 Huángchá</td><td>Light</td><td>Junshan Yinzhen, Huoshan Huangya</td><td>Mellow, smooth, rare</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Oolong</td><td>烏龍茶 Wūlóngchá</td><td>Partial (15-85%)</td><td>Tieguanyin, Da Hong Pao, Dong Ding</td><td>Complex, floral to roasted</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Red (Black)</td><td>紅茶 Hóngchá</td><td>Full</td><td>Keemun, Lapsang Souchong, Dianhong</td><td>Malty, sweet, robust</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Dark (Pu-erh)</td><td>黑茶 Hēichá</td><td>Post-fermented</td><td>Sheng Pu-erh, Shu Pu-erh, Liu Bao</td><td>Earthy, aged, deep</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>All six categories come from the same plant species. It is the <em>processing method</em> &mdash; withering, fixing, rolling, oxidation, and drying &mdash; that determines a tea's category, flavour, and character.</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>中國茶的六大分類</h2>
      <p>中國茶依加工程度與方式分為六大類，其中<strong>氧化程度</strong>是最關鍵的區分標準：</p>
      <table class="elements-table">
        <thead><tr><th>類別</th><th>中文</th><th>氧化程度</th><th>著名品種</th><th>風味特徵</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>綠茶</td><td>綠茶 Lǜchá</td><td>不氧化</td><td>Longjing, Biluochun, Huangshan Maofeng</td><td>清新、草本、甘甜</td></tr>
          <tr><td>白茶</td><td>白茶 Báichá</td><td>極輕微</td><td>Silver Needle, White Peony</td><td>淡雅、細膩、蜜香</td></tr>
          <tr><td>黃茶</td><td>黃茶 Huángchá</td><td>輕度</td><td>Junshan Yinzhen, Huoshan Huangya</td><td>醇和、順滑、珍稀</td></tr>
          <tr><td>烏龍茶</td><td>烏龍茶 Wūlóngchá</td><td>部分（15-85%）</td><td>Tieguanyin, Da Hong Pao, Dong Ding</td><td>層次豐富，花香至焙火香</td></tr>
          <tr><td>紅茶</td><td>紅茶 Hóngchá</td><td>全氧化</td><td>Keemun, Lapsang Souchong, Dianhong</td><td>麥香、甘甜、醇厚</td></tr>
          <tr><td>黑茶（普洱）</td><td>黑茶 Hēichá</td><td>後發酵</td><td>Sheng Pu-erh, Shu Pu-erh, Liu Bao</td><td>陳韻、醇厚、深沉</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>六大類茶皆源自同一植物品種。正是<em>加工方法</em> &mdash; 萎凋、殺青、揉捻、氧化與乾燥 &mdash; 決定了茶的類別、滋味與風格。</p>
</div>
